<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Rainbow Colors</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      text-align: center;
      padding: 50px;
      background-color: <%= color %>;
    }
    h1 {
      font-size: 3rem; /* Increased font size */
      color: #333;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }
    .container {
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 20px;
      background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8); /* Semi-transparent white background */
      border-radius: 10px;
      box-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    }
    ul {
      list-style-type: none;
      padding: 0;
    }
    li {
      font-size: 1.5rem; /* Increased font size */
      margin: 15px 0;
      padding: 10px;
      background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9); /* Semi-transparent white background */
      border-radius: 5px;
      box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    }
    .color-callout {
      font-size: 2rem; /* Increased font size */
      font-weight: bold;
      margin-top: 30px;
      color: #333;
      padding: 15px;
      background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9); /* Semi-transparent white background */
      border-radius: 5px;
    }
    .fun-facts {
      text-align: left;
      margin-top: 30px;
      font-size: 1.2rem;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }
    .fun-facts h2 {
      font-size: 2rem;
      color: #333;
      margin-bottom: 15px;
    }
    .fun-facts p {
      margin-bottom: 15px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Colors of the Rainbow</h1>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Red</strong> - The color of passion and energy.</li>
      <li><strong>Orange</strong> - The color of creativity and enthusiasm.</li>
      <li><strong>Yellow</strong> - The color of happiness and optimism.</li>
      <li><strong>Green</strong> - The color of nature and growth.</li>
      <li><strong>Blue</strong> - The color of calm and trust.</li>
      <li><strong>Indigo</strong> - The color of intuition and perception.</li>
      <li><strong>Violet</strong> - The color of spirituality and imagination.</li>
    </ul>

    <!-- Display the current color -->
    <div class="color-callout" id="colorCallout"></div>

    <!-- Fun Facts Section -->
    <div class="fun-facts">
      <h2>Fun Facts About Rainbows</h2>
      <p>
        A rainbow is a meteorological phenomenon caused by reflection, refraction, and dispersion of light in water droplets, resulting in a spectrum of light appearing in the sky.
      </p>
      <p>
        Did you know? A double rainbow occurs when light is reflected twice inside a raindrop. The second rainbow is fainter and has its colors reversed!
      </p>
      <p>
        Rainbows are actually full circles, but we usually only see the upper half because the ground blocks the lower half.
      </p>
      <p>
        The colors of the rainbow are always in the same order: red, orange, yellow, green, blue, indigo, and violet.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script>
    // Function to call out the current color
    function callOutColor() {
      const color = "<%= color %>"; // Get the color from the server-side template
      const colorCallout = document.getElementById('colorCallout');

      // Display the current color
      colorCallout.textContent = `The current background color is: ${color.toUpperCase()}`;
    }

    // Call the function when the page loads
    callOutColor();
  </script>
</body>
</html>